        </Grid>
        <Grid HorizontalAlignment="Left" Height="240" Margin="88,322,0,0" VerticalAlignment="Top" Width="727">
            <Label Content="DESCRIPTION:" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Height="30" Margin="16,33,0,0" VerticalAlignment="Top" Width="129" Foreground="#FFFDFDFD" FontSize="16" FontWeight="Bold"/>
            <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Left" Height="139" Margin="20,78,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Width="697" Foreground="#FFFFCE5C" FontSize="16" FontWeight="Bold" TextAlignment="Justify"><Run Text="Control Systems Engineering studies how to model, analyze, and design feedback "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="control systems.  It focuses on maintaining desired outputs despite disturbances or "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="changes in inputs.  Key topics include system stability, time and frequency response, and "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="controller design.  This field is crucial for automation in industries like robotics, aerospace, "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="and manufacturing.  Engineers learn to make systems respond predictably and reliably"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="using control theory principles."/></TextBlock>
        </Grid>

    </Grid>
